                    <label for="probability">Probability (Area under curve)</label>
                    <div class="value-display" id="probability-value">0.3989</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section class="section">
            <h2>Applications of Normal Distribution</h2>
            <p>The normal distribution has numerous applications across various fields:</p>
            
            <div class="applications-grid">
                <div class="application-card">
                    <h3>Quality Control</h3>
                    <p>Manufacturing processes often follow a normal distribution, allowing quality control engineers to set acceptable ranges for product dimensions.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="application-card">
                    <h3>Finance</h3>
                    <p>Stock returns, while not perfectly normal, are often modeled using normal distribution for risk assessment and portfolio management.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="application-card">
                    <h3>Psychology</h3>
                    <p>Many psychological traits like IQ scores, personality traits, and reaction times follow a normal distribution in the population.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="application-card">
                    <h3>Medicine</h3>
                    <p>Biological measurements like blood pressure, cholesterol levels, and height often follow a normal distribution in healthy populations.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="application-card">
                    <h3>Social Sciences</h3>
                    <p>Test scores, survey responses, and many other measurements in social sciences tend to follow a normal distribution.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="application-card">
                    <h3>Meteorology</h3>
                    <p>Weather measurements like temperature, rainfall, and atmospheric pressure often follow normal distributions over time.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section class="section">
